{
  "stem": "1343.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Is it OK now?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So let me go now to the labor camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the forced labor camp, I met up with one of my uncles, with whom I was together from that point on, which is June 1944 until after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Frank Ferenc Friedman, my mother's brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the-- he was extremely religious, even more so than I was, maybe even my father was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he, unfortunately, had took it upon himself that he ate nothing but kosher in the first six months in the forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in the labor camp-- let me say this, that it was an interesting situation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were under Hungarian guards, but working for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We lived-- what they made us to live in, in a stable, in a former-- we had stable.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And Hungarian guards took us out to the workplace, which was some four miles from where we slept.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there we were under German supervision and guidance.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "First day when we arrived with the Hungarians, two German, very lowly ranked soldiers-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--took us over and asked, in German-- and the Hungarians don't speak German, only us Jews spoke with them-- and asked one of our Jewish leaders, who are those guys with the weapons behind us?",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they told them, they are our guards.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He said, well, tell them that either they should take some tools also and work with us, or get the hell out of here.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when we-- when the Jewish guys translated it to the Hungarian lieutenant, he turned around and wanted to kick the Jew in the [LAUGHTER] behind.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
